    introduction: "Welcome to Strength Training for Recovery. There is something uniquely powerful about picking up something heavy and putting it down again. Strength training is one of the most effective tools for recovery because it provides immediate, tangible feedback — you are either stronger this week than last week, or you are not. In a recovery journey filled with ambiguity and slow progress, this clarity is invaluable. Research shows that resistance training reduces depression symptoms by 45 percent, increases dopamine and serotonin production, improves sleep architecture, and builds the discipline and routine that recovery demands. This course will teach you how to train safely, progressively, and sustainably. You do not need a gym membership or fancy equipment to start — a set of resistance bands and your own body weight will carry you far.",
